            "comments": [
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 18,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Zhikui Ren",
                        "email": "zhikui.ren@intel.com",
                        "username": "ZhikuiRen"
                    },
                    "message": "We should be able to read the current state before the polling. Have you looked into read line status in constructor?"
                },
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 18,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Chau Ly",
                        "email": "chaul@amperecomputing.com",
                        "username": "chaul-ampere"
                    },
                    "message": "We can, but I see that it makes this type stand out from the others because they should all be able to call readSensor() as their own way to read. Moreover, I think let them 3 all use timer polling will make pollSensorStatus() to be implemented by the base class instead of being overriden by the 3 and also get rid of the need to read the intial state.\n\nI'm not sure if there will be other types coming that prefer another method to poll over using timer. Do you suggest that I should leave it like that and just read the initial state for this type in its constructor?"
                },
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 18,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Zhikui Ren",
                        "email": "zhikui.ren@intel.com",
                        "username": "ZhikuiRen"
                    },
                    "message": "I do think for system implemented the intrusion with GPIO and supports interrupt. Take advantage of the hardware capability makes the code more efficient.\n\n> make pollSensorStatus() to be implemented by the base class instead of being overriden by the 3\n\nI don't understand why it can not be only overridden by GPIOSensor type"
                },
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 18,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Chau Ly",
                        "email": "chaul@amperecomputing.com",
                        "username": "chaul-ampere"
                    },
                    "message": "You're right about the hw ability we should enlist. Updated to just initially update value for GPIO type and let pollSensorStatus be overridden by the GPIO class only, other classes will directly use the definition in the base class."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 18,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Zhikui Ren",
                        "email": "zhikui.ren@intel.com",
                        "username": "ZhikuiRen"
                    },
                    "message": "Done"
                },
                {
